{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|とわ}}
{{IPAchar|/toba/}} → {{IPAchar|/towa/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|-}}. Appears in the ''{{w|Tales of Ise}}'', likely dating to the early 900s CE. Pronounced as ''toba'' until the later {{w|Heian period}}.<ref name="KDJ"/>

Ultimate derivation {{unk|ja|sort=とわ|nocap=1}}. May be a contraction of earlier ''tokotoba'' (see above),<ref name="KDJ"/> or may have been an independent term used to form ''tokotoba'' as a compound.<ref name="SMK5"/>

